BLIST.ITEM:
Empty map:
{}

{}

Some examples of literals:
{:first-name "Charlie"

 :last-name "McFishwich"}

#<core$_GT_ clojure.core$_GT_@15cfd851>
{"string-key" +}

{"string-key" #<core$_PLUS_ clojure.core$_PLUS_@658d00be>

Maps can be created with the hash-map function
(hash-map :a 1 :b 2)

{:a 1 :b 2}

Literal:
#{"kurt vonnegut" 20 :icicle}

#{:icicle "kurt vonnegut" 20}

Hash sets can also be created with the hash-ser function.
(hash-set 1 1 2 2)

#{1 2}

Elements can be added with the conj function.
(conj #{:a :b} :c)

#{:a :b :c}
